Package datastructures.trees

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    BinarySearchTree<T extends java.lang.Comparable<T>>
    A BinarySearchTree is a Tree with a maximum of 2 children nodes per node which allows for adding and removing nodes in a sorted manner.
    MaxHeap<T extends java.lang.Comparable<T>>
    MaxHeaps are complete binary search trees whose node contents are always larger than the contents of their children nodes.
    MinHeap<T extends java.lang.Comparable<T>>
    MinHeaps are complete binary search trees whose node contents are always smaller than the contents of their children nodes.
    Tree<T extends java.lang.Comparable<T>>
    A standard interface for a Tree data structure.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ArrayMaxHeap<T extends java.lang.Comparable<T>>
    An implementation of a MaxHeap using an underlying array.
    ArrayMinHeap<T extends java.lang.Comparable<T>>
    ArrayMinHeap is a MinHeap based on an internal array.
    AVLBinarySearchTree<T extends java.lang.Comparable<T>>
    AVLBinarySearchTree is an implementation of an Adelskon - Velskii - Landis (AVL) BST.
    LinkedBinarySearchTree<T extends java.lang.Comparable<T>>
    LinkedBinarySearchTree is an implementation of a BinarySearchTree using links.
    LinkedMaxHeap<T extends java.lang.Comparable<T>>
    A MaxHeap is a tree (specifically, a complete binary tree) where every node is larger than or equal to its descendants (as defined by the compareTo() overridings of the type T).
    LinkedMinHeap<T extends java.lang.Comparable<T>>
    A MinHeap is a tree (specifically, a complete binary tree) where every node is smaller than or equal to its descendants (as defined by the compareTo() overridings of the type T).
    RedBlackBinarySearchTree<T extends java.lang.Comparable<T>>
    RedBlackBinarySearchTree is a binary tree-based implementation of 2-3 trees.
